  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-10 min or until fork-tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot to steam-dry</p><p>Reboil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1660038124125-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1660038124125-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1660038124125-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1660038124125-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1660038124125-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>lean pork</strong> <strong>mince</strong> (remove the paper if required) with the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>, <strong>half </strong>the<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>chicken stock mix</strong> (you'll use the rest later) and a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>then mix thoroughly with clean hands until fully combined, then shape into 12 <span class=\"text-danger\">[24]</span> <strong>meatballs</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>meatballs</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min on each side or until browned</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1660038129079-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1660038129079-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1660038129079-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1660038129079-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1660038129079-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>remaining chicken</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong>, <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>Henderson's Relish</strong> and<strong> redcurrent jelly</strong> in 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>stock</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>dried cranberries</strong> to a bowl and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the meatballs have browned, transfer them to a plate (reserving the pan) and set aside, these will finish cooking in the sauce later</p>",
